Instructions to Run the Movie Recommendation System 
Follow these steps to set up and run the Movie Recommendation System project built with Streamlit:

Prerequisites:
Python 3.x: Ensure Python is installed on your system.

Pip: Python's package installer.

Dataset Files: Download the following files and place them in the project directory:

tmdb_5000_movies.csv

tmdb_5000_credits.csv

Step 1: Clone the Repository
Open a terminal or command prompt.

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/Aastha02-jan/movie-recommendation-system.git
Navigate to the project directory:

cd movie-recommendation-system
Step 2: Install Dependencies
Install the required Python libraries using pip:

pip install pandas numpy scikit-learn nltk streamlit

Step 3: Run the Streamlit App
Start the Streamlit app by running:

streamlit run app.py
A new browser window/tab will open automatically, displaying the Movie Recommendation System interface.

Step 4: Use the Application
Enter a Movie Title:

In the input box, type the name of a movie (e.g., Avatar).

Get Recommendations:

Click the "Recommend" button.

The system will display a list of 5 recommended movies similar to the one you entered.

Example:
Input: Avatar

Output:

Guardians of the Galaxy

Aliens

Star Wars: The Clone Wars

Star Trek Beyond

The Avengers
